// ── Demo finished-page screenshot (inlined, full page, full resolution) ───────
// A full-resolution render of a real Adobe page, inlined as a base64 JPEG data URI
// so the result preview can SCROLL through the whole finished page in the stubbed
// demo. Inlined (not a bundled asset) on purpose: da-playground only symlinks
// page-forge.{js,css,html}, so an emitted /tools/assets/*.jpg would 404 under
// ?ref=local. A data URI rides inside page-forge.js and resolves identically on
// :5173, ?ref=local, and headless. It's ~3MB, which is fine: this whole module
// tree-shakes out of a normal client:build (demo-only). Real sessions leave
// Session.previewImage undefined and fall back to the generic skeleton.
// Production end state is <iframe src={liveHref}> (see ResultCard PagePreview).
// Regenerate: sips -s format jpeg -s formatOptions 82 <src>.png --out x.jpg; base64.
export const DEMO_PAGE_IMAGE = 'data:image/jpeg;base64,';
